---
description: Data engineering principles
alwaysApply: true
---
- Idempotency: every pipeline step must be re-runnable without side effects.
- Schema-on-read at bronze (preserve raw fidelity); schema-on-write at silver and gold (enforce contracts).
- Bronze: raw + ingestion metadata only (load_ts, source_file, source_system, dw_row_hash). No business logic. No deduplication.
- Silver: cleansed, deduplicated, conformed types. Pydantic-validated at write time. Schema enforced.
- Gold: Kimball star schema (facts + conformed dimensions). Built in dbt.
- Use Delta Lake for all layers. MERGE for upserts, never INSERT OVERWRITE on dimension tables.
- Dimension SCD2 is implemented via dbt snapshots (which manage __start_at / __end_at / is_current automatically).
- Surrogate keys: hash-based on (natural_key + scd_start_date) for SCD2 dimensions; hash on natural_key for SCD1. Deterministic, parallelisable, no central sequence needed.
- Facts are insert-only (transactional or periodic snapshot). They carry load_ts and source provenance, NOT valid_from/valid_to/is_current. Accumulating-snapshot facts are the rare exception and still don't keep history.
- Facts reference the dimension surrogate key valid at the event timestamp, not the current surrogate key. This is what makes historical reports render correctly.
- Tests: every dbt model has at least not_null and unique tests on its grain. Every fact has a referential-integrity test against its dimensions.
